<p>New Mexico presents exceptional opportunities for both solar energy and efficient HVAC systems, making it one of the most attractive states for homeowners seeking energy independence and cost savings. With an average of 5.8 peak sun hours per day and over 310 sunny days annually, the Land of Enchantment ranks among the top states in the nation for solar potential. This abundant sunshine, combined with New Mexico's average electricity rate of 12.8¬¢ per kilowatt-hour, creates compelling economics for residential solar installations that can significantly reduce or eliminate monthly electric bills.</p>

